It should never break a name
printWidth: 1
{% function res = block %}
{%- function res = 'partial' -%}

It should break on named args
printWidth: 1
{% function res = 'foo/bar',
  key1: val1,
  key2: (0..1)
%}

It should not require commas (as per syntax) but add them when pretty printed
{% function res = 'foo/bar', key1: val1, key2: (0..1) %}

It should not require spaces (as per syntax) but add them when pretty printed
{% function res = 'foo/bar', key1: val1, key2: (0..1) %}

It should strip trailing commas by default
{% function res = 'foo' %}
{% function res = 'foo', product: product %}

It should format hash-access result variable
{% function hash.key = 'partial' %}

It should format dot-access result variable
{% function obj.prop = 'partial' %}

It should format variable partial
{% function res = partial_name %}
